TSX-listed Victoria Gold Corporation has exceeded its full-year guidance for 2021 by 2 222 oz of gold, producing 164 222 oz. This was a 40% increase in production compared with 2020, and while 2022 will undoubtedly present new challenges, CEO John McConnell says its operations will continue to grow steadily. Victoria owns 100% of the Dublin Gulch gold property, in the Yukon Territory, containing the company’s Eagle and Olive Gold deposits.